        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:23PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 223 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Dierks, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dierks, Lockesburg, Lebanon and Provo.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
